(Kim Dan)

564
00:38:36,460 --> 00:38:37,870
How could a man in his 20s be here?

565
00:38:44,950 --> 00:38:46,320
What was that guy?

566
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:47,720
That was upsetting.

567
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:55,030
Would you like to say anything before we finish?

568
00:38:55,030 --> 00:38:57,580
Please hire me.

569
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:00,260
I like your enthusiasm.

570
00:39:00,660 --> 00:39:02,730
I'll assist the young lady as best I can

571
00:39:07,350 --> 00:39:09,460
so that she could shine brightly.

572
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:13,070
I want to see you

573
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:14,740
shine brightly

574
00:39:15,270 --> 00:39:16,720
like you did then

575
00:39:17,110 --> 00:39:18,480
just one more time.

576
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:26,130
What did you just say?

577
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:29,920
Please. Please be effective.

578
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:33,920
Shine brightly.

579
00:39:40,260 --> 00:39:41,360
Shine brightly.

580
00:39:41,930 --> 00:39:43,250
You'll shine brightly and sparkle.

581
00:39:43,250 --> 00:39:44,260
Stop.

582
00:39:49,540 --> 00:39:50,640
That's enough. Leave.

583
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:55,440
Did I do something wrong?

584
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:57,070
If you tell me what I did...

585
00:39:57,070 --> 00:39:58,960
Your interview is over, so leave.

586
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:01,820
I have no place to go if I don't get this job.

587
00:40:02,130 --> 00:40:03,360
My dad kicked me out.

588
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:05,070
And my uncle won't even help.

589
00:40:05,210 --> 00:40:07,580
I'm all alone in this harsh world.

590
00:40:08,150 --> 00:40:09,250
So what?

591
00:40:12,470 --> 00:40:14,890
I was hoping you could help me.

592
00:40:32,350 --> 00:40:33,980
I thought she would be dejected,

593
00:40:33,980 --> 00:40:35,430
but she's still cranky.

594
00:40:35,650 --> 00:40:37,460
They say you can't fix humans.

595
00:40:37,630 --> 00:40:39,000
Gosh, that temper of hers.

596
00:40:39,790 --> 00:40:40,760
Excuse me.

597
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:47,490
I just said that out loud, didn't I?

598
00:40:51,850 --> 00:40:53,120
I totally forgot for a second.

599
00:40:55,940 --> 00:40:57,350
Since you already heard it,

600
00:40:57,350 --> 00:40:58,490
I'll say one more thing.

601
00:40:59,110 --> 00:41:01,350
Be nice, okay?

602
00:41:01,790 --> 00:41:03,950
Be shiny. Be nice!

603
00:41:10,810 --> 00:41:11,820
What was that about?

604
00:41:14,290 --> 00:41:16,970
Hey! Stop right there!

605
00:41:17,630 --> 00:41:18,640
Young Lady!

606
00:41:20,270 --> 00:41:21,280
You just

607
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:23,390
walked on your own, right?

608
00:41:33,820 --> 00:41:35,100
Gosh, I'm in trouble now!

609
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:37,120
This is crazy. I guess I really am a human now!

610
00:41:37,390 --> 00:41:39,060
Should I go back and apologize?

611
00:41:39,060 --> 00:41:40,030
But I don't want to.

612
00:41:40,030 --> 00:41:41,870
Then I'll dissipate. Gosh! I don't want that.

613
00:41:42,050 --> 00:41:43,020
Yes.

614
00:41:43,330 --> 00:41:44,510
I should go back, apologize to her,

615
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:46,010
and go to paradise.

616
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:48,960
Gosh! I don't think I can do this.

617
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:50,370
- What do I do? / - Mr. Kim Dan!

618
00:41:50,370 --> 00:41:51,860
What should I do? I'm so torn!

619
00:41:58,950 --> 00:41:59,960
All right.

620
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:02,640
Use this phone while on duty.

621
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:03,740
And put this next to your bed.

622
00:42:03,740 --> 00:42:05,680
Whenever it rings, you must run to Young Lady.

623
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:07,220
This is an alarm for when she's going out.

624
00:42:07,220 --> 00:42:08,540
When it rings, run to where she is.

625
00:42:08,540 --> 00:42:09,730
This is her baby journal,

626
00:42:09,730 --> 00:42:10,780
and this is the critiques of her ballet.

627
00:42:10,780 --> 00:42:12,280
And this is a list of things that she hates,

628
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:13,990
and this is for the corneal transplant.

629
00:42:13,990 --> 00:42:15,670
And most importantly,

630
00:42:16,020 --> 00:42:17,290
here's your contract.

631
00:42:21,650 --> 00:42:23,190
I have to go through all of these things?

632
00:42:23,590 --> 00:42:24,600
Yes.

633
00:42:24,860 --> 00:42:25,870
By the way,

634
00:42:26,670 --> 00:42:27,810
where's your stuff?

635
00:42:28,290 --> 00:42:29,530
Is this it?

636
00:42:31,240 --> 00:42:33,350
You must be a terrible son.

637
00:42:33,350 --> 00:42:35,030
I guess you got kicked out empty-handed.

638
00:42:38,150 --> 00:42:39,870
I will return home eventually.

639
00:42:42,070 --> 00:42:43,080
Well, then.

640
00:42:43,300 --> 00:42:44,880
Thanks to you, I can call it a day.

641
00:42:45,100 --> 00:42:46,110
Take it easy.

642
00:43:03,630 --> 00:43:05,030
I got closer to her.

643
00:43:06,490 --> 00:43:07,500
Yes.

644
00:43:17,400 --> 00:43:19,690
Mr. Kim Dan is all moved in now.

645
00:43:21,670 --> 00:43:22,680
You may leave, then.

646
00:43:28,490 --> 00:43:30,730
The exact opposite of Mr. Jo could be better

647
00:43:31,210 --> 00:43:33,370
than someone who is sort of but not quite like him.

648
00:43:33,370 --> 00:43:34,600
I don't believe it.

649
00:43:35,130 --> 00:43:37,510
The spiel about the teddy bear and so on.

650
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:40,890
- I don't believe it. / - But earlier, you took...

651
00:43:40,890 --> 00:43:42,260
That was it, though.

652
00:43:43,310 --> 00:43:45,120
It's all in my mind anyway,

653
00:43:45,120 --> 00:43:46,660
so I should just overcome it.

654
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:50,310
I will do it on my own.

655
00:43:50,750 --> 00:43:51,720
Then

656
00:43:52,690 --> 00:43:54,930
why did you hire Mr. Kim?

657
00:44:05,670 --> 00:44:06,680
(Love)

658
00:44:11,870 --> 00:44:13,150
What...

659
00:44:13,410 --> 00:44:14,550
What's this sound?

660
00:44:14,860 --> 00:44:16,490
Gosh! Where's it coming from?

661
00:44:29,950 --> 00:44:31,230
What can I do for you?

662
00:44:31,230 --> 00:44:32,730
You're too slow. You must show up

663
00:44:32,730 --> 00:44:34,220
within a minute.

664
00:44:43,640 --> 00:44:45,220
Is it not the right side?

665
00:44:45,710 --> 00:44:46,810
I read that you always stand

666
00:44:46,810 --> 00:44:49,180
on the right side, so I should offer my left arm.

667
00:44:51,430 --> 00:44:53,050
Gosh, don't.

668
00:44:53,850 --> 00:44:55,250
Come on.

669
00:44:55,910 --> 00:44:57,540
Here, hold my arm.

670
00:45:13,510 --> 00:45:15,930
Oh, look at you! You're walking!

671
00:45:19,850 --> 00:45:21,430
You don't need to thank me.

672
00:45:21,610 --> 00:45:22,750
Since this already happened,

673
00:45:22,750 --> 00:45:24,250
you should try to recover quickly.

674
00:45:24,250 --> 00:45:25,830
Then you'll feel better,

675
00:45:25,830 --> 00:45:27,990
and with the gentle spring breeze...

676
00:45:27,990 --> 00:45:28,960
Be quiet.

677
00:45:30,720 --> 00:45:32,130
I hate noise.

678
00:45:33,140 --> 00:45:34,150
Just walk.

679
00:45:37,230 --> 00:45:38,460
Where are you going?

680
00:45:52,540 --> 00:45:53,550
You're so bad at this.

681
00:45:53,550 --> 00:45:55,450
Why does a secretary have to learn to do this?

682
00:45:55,450 --> 00:45:56,940
Please teach him well.

683
00:45:56,940 --> 00:45:59,190
His bones will break if he and I have a match.

684
00:46:00,240 --> 00:46:01,390
Teach him the pinning technique.

685
00:46:06,180 --> 00:46:08,030
Let go. Let go of me!

686
00:46:09,090 --> 00:46:10,050
I'm doomed.

687
00:46:10,190 --> 00:46:11,290
There isn't

688
00:46:11,290 --> 00:46:13,880
a single ounce of love in this woman.

689
00:46:15,990 --> 00:46:16,960
The piano.

690
00:46:22,460 --> 00:46:23,430
Get out.

691
00:46:26,820 --> 00:46:27,920
The corridor!

692
00:46:33,860 --> 00:46:35,750
You call this cleaning?

693
00:46:35,750 --> 00:46:38,390
Do better. Clean properly!

694
00:46:39,220 --> 00:46:41,160
Were human beings really made

695
00:46:41,510 --> 00:46:43,760
into the reflection of the deity?

696
00:46:48,600 --> 00:46:50,490
You can't even add up the calories correctly?

697
00:46:51,940 --> 00:46:52,950
I won't eat this.

698
00:46:53,000 --> 00:46:55,640
Then why is she so condescending

699
00:46:55,770 --> 00:46:57,440
and rude?

700
00:47:00,960 --> 00:47:02,980
My, these smell amazing. Smell these flowers.

701
00:47:07,960 --> 00:47:09,410
She doesn't know how to be impressed,

702
00:47:09,410 --> 00:47:11,120
and she's incapable of being marveled.

703
00:47:11,210 --> 00:47:14,030
There are 198 things on her dislike list.

704
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:18,430
No one in this mansion loves her.

705
00:47:19,440 --> 00:47:20,450
That includes me.

706
00:47:24,020 --> 00:47:25,290
But wait and see.

707
00:47:25,820 --> 00:47:27,670
No matter what happens,

708
00:47:28,860 --> 00:47:29,820
I'll be sure

709
00:47:30,400 --> 00:47:32,020
to make you fall in love.

710
00:48:32,130 --> 00:48:35,300
When I was the only principal dancer here,

711
00:48:35,300 --> 00:48:37,540
my dear Geum Nina was my understudy.

712
00:48:37,760 --> 00:48:39,210
In other words, she was my shadow.

713
00:48:40,310 --> 00:48:42,070
You're a 16th note faster.

714
00:48:43,480 --> 00:48:45,720
If you die, get sad,

715
00:48:45,720 --> 00:48:47,840
and fall in love before the music,

716
00:48:48,580 --> 00:48:50,560
it's rushed and kills the expectations.

717
00:49:00,200 --> 00:49:02,180
I thought being rushed was your only problem,

718
00:49:02,180 --> 00:49:03,590
but you're actually dumb.

719
00:49:17,760 --> 00:49:19,120
Do you want to break your ankle?

720
00:49:19,380 --> 00:49:21,010
You know what "next time" means

721
00:49:21,010 --> 00:49:22,680
to ballerinas.

722
00:49:23,430 --> 00:49:24,580
"I don't want to see your dance, ever."

723
00:49:24,580 --> 00:49:25,850
"You won't make it."

724
00:49:26,780 --> 00:49:30,030
You don't want to give me another chance.

725
00:49:31,480 --> 00:49:33,020
You've already made your decision.

726
00:49:34,830 --> 00:49:36,590
When I say "next time", I keep my word.

727
00:49:36,590 --> 00:49:37,730
I don't sugarcoat things.

728
00:50:04,040 --> 00:50:05,060
I'm back.

729
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:16,540
(Principal Dancer of Fantasia Ballet Company)

730
00:50:16,540 --> 00:50:17,730
(Geum Kichun, Choi Yeongja, Married)

731
00:50:17,730 --> 00:50:19,490
(Geum Runa, Associate Director)

732
00:50:20,500 --> 00:50:22,880
(Geum Nina, Principal Dancer)

733
00:50:25,210 --> 00:50:27,720
(Lee Yeonseo, regained her eyesight)

734
00:50:33,920 --> 00:50:34,890
How's she doing?

735
00:50:35,420 --> 00:50:36,690
She still can't walk?

736
00:50:38,630 --> 00:50:40,300
She can move around now

737
00:50:40,300 --> 00:50:41,710
after she hired a new secretary?

738
00:50:42,060 --> 00:50:43,120
Okay.

739
00:50:49,540 --> 00:50:50,820
Then should I

740
00:50:51,740 --> 00:50:53,100
get started now?

741
00:50:59,180 --> 00:51:00,890
Don't worry about it.

742
00:51:01,420 --> 00:51:03,710
Yeonseo just got surgery.

743
00:51:04,020 --> 00:51:05,820
And she took three years off.

744
00:51:05,820 --> 00:51:07,450
It won't be easy for her to return.

745
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:09,690
That surgery!

746
00:51:11,450 --> 00:51:12,680
How did you manage it that she could

747
00:51:12,680 --> 00:51:15,100
receive corneas after a car accident?

748
00:51:15,720 --> 00:51:17,830
I had no idea that Mr. Jo designated her

749
00:51:17,830 --> 00:51:19,330
as the receiver.

750
00:51:19,370 --> 00:51:21,840
You know that I tried to stop her

751
00:51:21,840 --> 00:51:23,240
from contacting a donor

752
00:51:23,240 --> 00:51:24,430
whenever there was one available.

753
00:51:24,430 --> 00:51:25,840
The biter is bitten.

754
00:51:26,940 --> 00:51:28,220
My gosh.

755
00:51:28,300 --> 00:51:29,800
The minister is also giving me pressure

756
00:51:29,800 --> 00:51:31,250
with her regaining eyesight.

757
00:51:31,560 --> 00:51:34,330
I mean, what if she asks for the foundation

758
00:51:34,950 --> 00:51:37,150
because she can see now?

759
00:51:37,190 --> 00:51:39,080
We should give it back. It was originally hers.

760
00:51:41,900 --> 00:51:43,570
You idiot.

761
00:51:43,840 --> 00:51:46,120
You can go back to your life in debt

762
00:51:46,120 --> 00:51:49,160
and make points to others for a living.

763
00:51:49,420 --> 00:51:52,370
But for me? I am not going back to that life.

764
00:51:58,880 --> 00:52:00,030
Did you check?

765
00:52:01,960 --> 00:52:03,590
I'm sure you'll find something.

766
00:52:04,780 --> 00:52:05,750
What?

767
00:52:06,630 --> 00:52:08,920
His articles are still left behind?

768
00:52:15,820 --> 00:52:18,550
Then we should clean it out for her.

769
00:52:21,590 --> 00:52:23,790
Hey!

770
00:52:31,440 --> 00:52:32,850
Who's in charge of the garden today?

771
00:52:34,220 --> 00:52:36,240
I just stepped on wet petals, slipped,

772
00:52:36,240 --> 00:52:38,260
and almost cracked my head open.

773
00:52:38,260 --> 00:52:39,410
Who was in charge?

774
00:52:42,270 --> 00:52:44,160
- You should stop. / - Don't get into this.

775
00:52:44,250 --> 00:52:45,660
I'll clean up the garden.

776
00:52:45,660 --> 00:52:47,860
I'll pick up every single petal left here.

777
00:52:47,860 --> 00:52:48,960
Happy?

778
00:52:50,720 --> 00:52:52,340
You can go back.

779
00:52:53,710 --> 00:52:54,980
Do not go back.

780
00:53:00,530 --> 00:53:01,850
This is a stretch of your authority.

781
00:53:01,850 --> 00:53:03,560
Do you want me to read over the contract?

782
00:53:03,560 --> 00:53:05,500
I haven't signed it yet anyway.

783
00:53:05,500 --> 00:53:07,440
While we're on it, should we look into the laws

784
00:53:07,440 --> 00:53:08,620
on the overuse of power by an employer?

785
00:53:08,620 --> 00:53:10,960
I'll go into every single detail on that.

786
00:53:12,320 --> 00:53:14,780
Go back inside. Come on, go back.

787
00:53:15,970 --> 00:53:17,160
Yes, go.

788
00:53:19,100 --> 00:53:20,110
You!

789
00:53:24,460 --> 00:53:25,700
You hate the sunset, don't you?

790
00:53:26,800 --> 00:53:27,760
- What? / - You always

791
00:53:27,760 --> 00:53:29,350
throw a fit during the sunset.

792
00:53:29,350 --> 00:53:31,720
What is it? Were you dumped at sunset?

793
00:53:31,990 --> 00:53:33,840
Did you see your first love having an affair

794
00:53:33,840 --> 00:53:35,200
under the red sky?

795
00:53:35,200 --> 00:53:36,430
What is it?

796
00:53:36,430 --> 00:53:39,070
Yes, the sunset always drives me crazy.

797
00:53:39,250 --> 00:53:40,790
I want to burn anyone that I see

798
00:53:40,790 --> 00:53:42,370
with the burning sun.

799
00:53:42,370 --> 00:53:43,340
Happy now?

800
00:53:44,920 --> 00:53:46,420
If you know better, why do you do that?

801
00:53:46,420 --> 00:53:49,590
You can only get over love with another love.

802
00:53:50,640 --> 00:53:52,050
Why don't you meet someone great

803
00:53:53,110 --> 00:53:54,960
before you go crazier?

804
00:53:56,410 --> 00:53:57,860
There is this saying too.

805
00:53:57,950 --> 00:53:59,710
"Even if we speak with the tongues of angels,"

806
00:53:59,710 --> 00:54:01,070
"even if we gain all the world and its knowledge,"

807
00:54:01,070 --> 00:54:02,830
"even if we sacrifice ourselves,"

808
00:54:02,830 --> 00:54:04,060
"without love,"

809
00:54:04,680 --> 00:54:05,870
"we have nothing."

810
00:54:08,510 --> 00:54:09,920
Come to think about it, I regret

811
00:54:10,580 --> 00:54:12,340
that I didn't ask for your religion in the interview.

812
00:54:14,360 --> 00:54:15,860
Make sure this place is spotless.

813
00:54:43,000 --> 00:54:44,630
Excuse me. I'll take this one.

814
00:55:01,440 --> 00:55:02,760
"Tongues of angels"?

815
00:55:05,620 --> 00:55:07,290
That crazy cult believer.

816
00:55:07,820 --> 00:55:09,620
You're neither a pervert nor a pickpocket.

817
00:55:09,800 --> 00:55:11,160
You were a crazy cult believer?

818
00:55:11,160 --> 00:55:12,830
Not everyone behaves like you

819
00:55:12,830 --> 00:55:14,550
after experiencing a tragedy.

820
00:55:16,180 --> 00:55:17,280
Could it be?

821
00:55:30,610 --> 00:55:33,560
This rain is exactly like Lee Yeonseo.

822
00:55:33,560 --> 00:55:35,190
No matter how much I sweep, this rain is

823
00:55:35,190 --> 00:55:36,640
making more petals fall down.

824
00:55:36,860 --> 00:55:38,710
In a word, it's useless.

825
00:55:38,710 --> 00:55:40,200
It's all in vain.

826
00:55:40,990 --> 00:55:42,010
I mean,

827
00:55:43,060 --> 00:55:44,560
she has nothing I can work with.

828
00:55:45,130 --> 00:55:47,550
If she likes something, I can start with that.

829
00:55:48,650 --> 00:55:50,230
Her soul is like Sodom and Gomorrah.

830
00:56:09,680 --> 00:56:11,310
What? Why are these out?

831
00:56:12,190 --> 00:56:13,330
What is this?

832
00:56:15,050 --> 00:56:16,190
What's going on?

833
00:56:17,470 --> 00:56:18,480
What is this?

834
00:56:22,710 --> 00:56:23,810
Gosh.

835
00:56:24,160 --> 00:56:25,520
(Noisy Gong)

836
00:56:25,740 --> 00:56:27,060
Darn it.

837
00:56:28,820 --> 00:56:30,980
(Kim Dan)

838
00:56:58,700 --> 00:56:59,890
She's gone.

839
00:57:37,990 --> 00:57:39,350
Gosh, darn it.

840
00:57:40,450 --> 00:57:42,920
Dismissed. Begone.

841
00:57:43,310 --> 00:57:45,290
My gosh, this is driving me crazy.

842
00:57:45,690 --> 00:57:46,830
